oice model, and start changing voices.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>macOS Installation in 3 Steps</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Unzip</strong> the <code>vcclient_mac_[version].zip</code> archive—this creates a folder.</li>\n<li>Inside, double-click <code>MMVCServerSIO_mac_onnxcpu.app</code> (first run may prompt “unidentified developer”; allow it in System Settings → Privacy & Security).</li>\n<li>Safari/Chrome launches the Okada GUI; grant microphone access when macOS asks.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>First-Run Checklist</h3>\n<p>• Wear headphones to avoid feedback loops.<br />• If you need to pipe audio into Discord/OBS, install a virtual cable (VB-Cable on Windows, BlackHole on macOS) and set Okada’s <strong>Output Device</strong> to that cable.<br />• Click <strong>Start</strong> in the GUI, speak, and hear your new voice instantly.</p>\n<p>[VISUAL SUGGESTION: Insert an image here that shows the Hugging Face file list with the two highlighted ZIPs ➜ one at ~3.7 GB (Windows) and one at ~500 MB (macOS). Alt text: \"Selecting the correct vcclient download on Hugging Face\".]</p>\n<h2>Adding Voice Models in Seconds</h2>\n<p>Need an English female, a cartoon robot, or a celebrity voice? The community maintains a giant <strong>Voice Models</strong> post with direct download links. Grab a model (<code>.pth</code> or <code>.onnx</code>) and drop it in the <code>models</code> folder, then click <em>Add</em> in the Okada GUI and select it. Switch voices live with zero downtime.</p>\n<h2>Tuning Okada for Real-Time Performance</h2>\n<h3>Chunk & Extra</h3>\n<p>Chunk 256–512, Extra 8192–16384 keeps latency under 200 ms on RTX 30-series cards.</p>\n<h3>F0 Engine</h3>\n<p>RMVPE = fastest + most natural; Harvest is solid cross-platform fallback.</p>\n<h3>Fine-Tune Pitch & Formant</h3>\n<p>Subtle ±1-2 semitones and slight formant shifts polish gender presentation.</p>\n<p>[VISUAL SUGGESTION: Insert an image here of the Okada settings page with Chunk, Extra, and F0 dropdown circled. Alt text: \"Latency controls in Okada Voice Changer\".]</p>\n<h2>Okada vs Voicemod vs Voice.ai</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Feature/Metric</th>\n<th>Okada (Free)</th>\n<th>Voicemod (Paid/Freemium)</th>\n<th>Voice.ai (Freemium)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Price & limits</td>\n<td>$0, unlimited use</td>\n<td>Subscription for full set</td>\n<td>Credits or GPU mining</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Voice realism</td>\n<td>⭐⭐⭐⭐☆ (model-dependent)</td>\n<td>⭐⭐☆☆☆ (DSP + few AI)</td>\n<td>⭐⭐⭐☆ (cloud AI)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Custom models</td>\n<td>Yes, any .pth/ONNX</td>\n<td>Very limited</td>\n<td>Marketplace voices</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Offline privacy</td>\n<td>100 % local</td>\n<td>Needs online login</td>\n<td>Requires internet</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ease of setup</td>\n<td>Tech-savvy</td>\n<td>Plug-and-play</td>\n<td>Easy installer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hardware load</td>\n<td>High GPU/CPU</td>\n<td>Light</td>\n<td>Medium</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Safety, Privacy & Responsible Use</h2>\n<p>Okada never transmits your mic audio off-device; the only internet traffic is downloading the ZIP and optional voice models. Always credit or obtain permission if you plan to monetize content using a recognisable celebrity voice.</p>\n<h2>Troubleshooting Cheat-Sheet</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Symptom</th>\n<th>Quick Fix</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Delay >1 s</td>\n<td>Lower Chunk, enable GPU, close background apps</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Robotic output</td>\n<td>Switch F0 engine, raise Extra, check mic gain</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Echo grows squeaky</td>\n<td>Use headphones, disable “listen to this device”</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>GUI won’t start</td>\n<td>Run as admin (Win) / allow in Security (Mac)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Conclusion & Next Steps</h2>\n<p>Invest an hour to install Okada and you’ll wield a studio-grade, real-time voice lab—free, private, and endlessly hackable. Download a few community models, save your favourite presets, and let your imagination take the mic.</p>\n<h2>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS (FAQ)</h2>\n<p><strong>QUESTION</strong>: Is Okada Voice Changer really free forever?<br /><strong>ANSWER</strong>: Yes—both the program and all core features are open-source with no subscriptions or usage caps.</p>\n<p><strong>QUESTION</strong>: Which ZIP do I download if I’m on Windows 11?<br /><strong>ANSWER</strong>: Always grab the latest <strong>vcclient_win_cuda_[version].zip</strong> (~3.7 GB) from the Hugging Face page. Newer version number = newer build.</p>\n<p><strong>QUESTION</strong>: Do I still need VB-Cable on Windows if I only want to hear myself?<br /><strong>ANSWER</strong>: No. VB-Cable is only required when you want other apps (Discord, OBS, Zoom) to hear the changed voice. For self-monitoring, set Okada’s output to your headphones directly.</p>\n<p><strong>QUESTION</strong>: Can I run Okada on older Intel Macs?<br /><strong>ANSWER</strong>: It will start, but performance is limited—expect noticeable latency without Apple-silicon acceleration. For best real-time results, use an M1/M2 Mac.</p>\n<p><strong>QUESTION</strong>: Where can I get more voices?<br /><strong>ANSWER</strong>: Check the community <strong>Voice Models</strong> post linked on the Okada GitHub/Hugging Face page—hundreds of user-trained voices are ready to drop into your <code>models</code> folder.</p>";
